author: Min Zeng
title: Debt Ceiling Standoff Hits Bond Market
text:
Concerns that the U.S. could run out of money next month rippled through the bond market Friday, marking a return to the worries of previous debt-ceiling standoffs.
The yield on the U.S. Treasury bill maturing on Nov. 12 jumped to 0.036% Friday, the highest level since Aug. 19 and up from 0.005% Thursday. Bond prices fall as their yields rise.
